GROW.🍃

a subtle reminder...
Patience been ah Pimp!
& it can Shape & Mold’ya...
to ah Solider or a Sucka...
hv u Live’n Off ah Loaf ah Peanut Butter & some Smuckers cuz u Shuck & u Jive...
& now u Jammed Up by a 9 to 5 that’s Suckin u Dry!
Zappin the Super Powers u Neva Identified...
Pedal Pluckin for Love’n...
u find it Hard to Decide...
BUT!
when ah “Side Chick” & “Thot” are Both an Actual Thing...
it’s Hard to Visualize the Dream we Learned from Doc King.🙏🏽 - Sol

💜gratitude.
. . . 
I wanna thank @mlivenews & @consumersenergy for providing a platform.🙏🏽
I have been working with MLive for the past 3 years…
Mentor Mondays…
Facilitating “SELF LOVE” sessions…
& this year I was blessed to close the Women’s Summit…
☝🏽wait there’s more…
when Governor @gewhitmer had an emergency & was no longer able to do the keynote for the “Women Shaping the State” dinner, I was asked to give the keynote last minute & with no hesitation…
I was the Keynote Speaker for the MLive & Consumers Energy 2023 “Women Shaping the State” Dinner!
. . .
“I ain’t BRAGGIN…
I’m jus Remind’n all the Grinders 
that the Dream can really HAPPEN!
that the Sky is very Vast & that every Bird can fly without not one of’em CRASHIN!”
i’m not here to compete or compare…
i’m here to remind you to DO THE WORK WITH YOUR WHOLE HEART & stay PREPARED!

I spent the last week making a record with one of my favorite emcees alive, Flint’s own @mamasolmusic. This project has been on the books for at least six years (!!!) and it was an incredible joy to make it happen at my house with my brothers @sputacular and @moogboogieman, who shared the production duties with me evenly.

I’ve never made an album with exactly zero preparation until this one. There were no audio demos, no pre-made beats to match up with lyrics… nothing. Mama Sol showed up with her lyrics and we showed up with our ears. We’d all sit in the control room together, listen to her do one of her songs a cappella, then go directly into the tracking room and cook up music to match it on the spot.

4 days and 12 songs later, we were done.

Aside from being SO DAMN FUN to work with my long-time running partners in this very different context, I can’t overemphasize how special this woman is. Artistically and linguistically, she’s operating on a level most rappers can only dream about. Concept, message, execution- it’s all there on 10. And as a human being, you’d be hard-pressed to find someone more inspiring. Born and bred in one of the toughest places in the US (Flint, Michigan), 2-time breast cancer survivor, single mother (of the year) of a kid on a full ride to college, school teacher for special education students, owner of the city’s first vegan cafe… it’s unbelievable. I just hope we do her justice when this thing is ready to go out into the world.

For now, all that’s left is editing and overdubs. I’ll post more when I get deeper into that process.
